SIMPLE: strobile
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Strobile
<hw>Strob"ile</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>strobilus</ets> a pine cone, Gr. <?/: cf. F.
<ets>strobole</ets>.]</ety> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>strobil</asp>.]</altsp> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A scaly
multiple fruit resulting from the ripening of an ament in certain
plants, as the hop or pine; a cone. See <er>Cone</er>, <pos>n.</pos>,
3.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>An individual asexually producing
sexual individuals differing from itself also in other respects, as the
tapeworm, -- one of the forms that occur in metagenesis.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Same as
<er>Strobila</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strobiliform</ent>⟦br⟧
